This was a little bit of Haiti.

00:44:41.130 --> 00:44:43.352
I wouldn't call it a
crisis issues or anything.

00:44:43.352 --> 00:44:45.560
But you're all trying to
make me go out at 12 o'clock

00:44:45.560 --> 00:44:47.310
on a business day.

00:44:47.310 --> 00:44:49.270
You all got us
working, you're right.

00:44:49.270 --> 00:44:50.610
It's not easy.

00:44:50.610 --> 00:44:51.621
But I didn't give up.

00:44:51.621 --> 00:44:52.870
You just put a little bit out.

00:44:52.870 --> 00:44:54.600
And the part that
Leah does, and I do,

00:44:54.600 --> 00:44:56.225
and anyone that's
been doing it awhile,

00:44:56.225 --> 00:44:59.290
is you pause after the
first three seconds.

00:44:59.290 --> 00:45:02.060
Give a little
something, and then wait

00:45:02.060 --> 00:45:03.820
to get the invitation.

00:45:03.820 --> 00:45:05.120
And that's breaking it down.

00:45:05.120 --> 00:45:06.670
That's news you can use.

00:45:06.670 --> 00:45:10.033
That's what you can all do a
little more starting today.

00:45:10.033 --> 00:45:12.650
Is you just put yourself
out there and then wait.

00:45:12.650 --> 00:45:15.756
And respond to what happens,
instead of agenda, A, B, C,

00:45:15.756 --> 00:45:19.890
D, I'm pretty sure when
you go into those places.

00:45:19.890 --> 00:45:22.680
AUDIENCE: Yeah we take note
of what the atmosphere is.

00:45:22.680 --> 00:45:26.480
So sometimes we show up
somewhere, there's a few folks

00:45:26.480 --> 00:45:27.870
to tell a story
better than I do,

00:45:27.870 --> 00:45:29.910
but sometimes we'll
show up to a hospital

00:45:29.910 --> 00:45:31.562
