just passed away.

00:45:31.562 --> 00:45:34.020
Or we'll finish the performance
and why we were performing,

00:45:34.020 --> 00:45:35.769
a child has passed
away in the other room.

00:45:35.769 --> 00:45:39.477
So we do rely on people
to give us the cues.

00:45:39.477 --> 00:45:41.685
And we do a soft clowning,
we do about loud clowning.

00:45:41.685 --> 00:45:44.101
So there are times when it's
appropriate to come out there

00:45:44.101 --> 00:45:46.861
with stilts and
drums and trombones

00:45:46.861 --> 00:45:48.110
and all these types of things.

00:45:48.110 --> 00:45:49.651
And then there's
also times when it's

00:45:49.651 --> 00:45:52.570
appropriate to do just very
quiet clowning and pulling

00:45:52.570 --> 00:45:54.240
a handkerchief out
of somebody's ear.

00:45:54.240 --> 00:45:56.340
You know, not even
making any sounds at all.

00:45:56.340 --> 00:45:59.406
And that's more like the
hospital type setting.

00:45:59.406 --> 00:46:01.780
And then the loud clowning is
more like the refugee camp,

00:46:01.780 --> 00:46:04.780
